# docmanage License

## Chapter 0. Definitions
**Article 0.** Definitions

(1) The Licensor is the legal entity owning the copyrighted works / the project

(2) The project, or copyrighted works, are the docmanage GitHub repository

(3) The Licensee is the legal entity agreeing to this license 

(4) Commerical use is either:

  (a) The use of a legal entity with the goal of obtaining profits

  (b) The use of a for-profit company with the goal of obtaining profits

  (c) Internal use of a for-profit company 

(5) Intent to contribute is defined as whether changes are contributed to The Project via Pull Request either within 4 months of the first modification, or within 14 days of the last substantial modification.

## Chapter I. Rights of Non-Commercial Use
**Article 1.** The Licensee may use the source code of the project for:

(1) Learning / Educational use

(2) Expanding upon the project, with or without the intent to contribute

**Article 2.** The Licensee may use the project's binaries:

(1) To link against them, either statically or dynamically, as long as the derived work / the rest of the project linking against said binaries is also licensed under this license

(2) For their intended use

## Chapter II. Rights of Commercial Use
**Article 3.** The Licensee may use the source code of the project for:

(1) Self-learning, or educational use only for themselves

(2) Expanding upon the project, with the intent to contribute

**Article 4.** The Licensee may not use the source code of the project for:

(1) Wide-spread educational use

(2) Expanding upon the project without the intent to contribute

**Article 5.** The Licensee may use the project's binaries:

(1) To link against them, either statically or dynamically, as long as the derived work / the rest of the project linking against said binaries is also licensed under this exact license, with the source code remaining open and available to anyone.

(2) For their intended use

## Chapter III. Rights of Distribution
**Article 6.** The Licensee may redistribute the project's source code, the project's binaries or other copyrighted works unmodified.

**Article 7.** The Licensee may redistribute the project's source code, the project's binaries or other copyrighted works that have been altered or modified, explicitly stating that they have been modified.

**Article 8.** The Licensee may not redistribute the project's source code, the project's binaries or other copyrighted works that have or have not been altered or modified without explicitly stating the original author (The Licensor) and the original project (The Project).

## Chapter IV. Disclaimers
**Article 9.** This software is provided as-is, without warranty of any kind.

**Article 10.** The Project Owner may not be held liable for any damages caused directly or indirectly by copyrighted works or The Project.

## Chapter V. EOC (End of Contract)
**Article 11.** The License to use copyrighted works granted upon this Agreement is immediately terminated upon:

(1) Repeated violation of its terms

(2) Violation of Chapter II, repeated or not

(3) Violation of Chapter III, Article 8, repeated or not

(4) Infringing on any applicable law, using the copyrighted works / The Project in the process, either directly or indirectly (where a connection can still clearly be made between The Project and the infringement of law)
